# Scheduler Conventions

## Market Hours

- Trading hours: 9:30 AM - 4:00 PM Eastern Time
- Check market status via Polygon `GET /v1/marketstatus/now` before each cycle
- Skip scans on market holidays (cache holiday calendar from Polygon at start of day)

## Scan Loop

Run continuously during market hours. Each cycle:

```
1. Check market status → skip if closed
2. Fetch stock market snapshot (all US stocks)
3. Fetch option chain snapshots (paginate through all underlyings)
4. Upsert to database
5. Score all contracts with meaningful activity
6. Apply already-priced-in gate
7. Send alerts for triggered signals
8. Log cycle stats (duration, contracts scanned, alerts fired/suppressed)
9. Begin next cycle immediately (no artificial delay)
```

## Resilience

- Wrap the full cycle in try/except — log errors, wait 60 seconds, retry
- If a single underlying's option chain fetch fails, log and continue to the next
- Track consecutive failures; alert operator (separate from trading alerts) after 5 consecutive cycle failures

## Startup & Shutdown

- On startup: verify DB connection, verify Polygon API key, fetch market calendar
- On shutdown (SIGINT/SIGTERM): complete current cycle, then exit cleanly
- Log start/stop events with timestamps
